TY  - JOUR
T1  - Aggregation and Optimization with State-Dependent Pricing: A Comment
AU  - Damjanovic, Vladislav
AU  - Nolan, Charles
Y1  - 2006/03/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/03/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2006.00672.x
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 565
EP  - 573
VL  - 74
IS  - 2
KW  - (S, s) pricing
KW  - money–output correlations
KW  - macroeconomic dynamics
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2006.00672.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - A key argument in Caplin and Leahy (1997) states that the correlation between monetary shocks and output is falling in the variance of the money supply. We demonstrate that this conclusion depends on solving for the correlation in the nonstationary state of the model. In the stationary state, that correlation is initially rising.
ER  - 

